> agent_manage
> ----------------------------------------------------------------------
> Discover agents, manage sessions, and browse workflows.
> 
> **Operations**: list_agents | list_sessions | get_log | create_session | resume_session | stop_session | cleanup_sessions | list_workflows
> 
> - `list_agents`: Returns all agents with their models, capabilities, and stable `model_id` identifiers. Use `model_id` from the response to start runs via `agent_run`.
> - `list_sessions`: Browse sessions. Returns `session_id` for each session. Filter by `state` (e.g. `failed`, `completed`, `running`). When called from agent mode, automatically scopes to sessions spawned by the current agent session.
> - `get_log`: Read transcript for a session. Returns transcript XML.
> - `create_session` / `resume_session`: Create or resume a session with a specific `model_id`.
> - `stop_session`: Stop a live session.
> - `cleanup_sessions`: Delete specific MCP-originated sessions by ID. Only sessions started via MCP are eligible; user-created sessions are never deleted. Skips active sessions. Use `list_sessions` first to find session IDs, then pass them here.
> - `list_workflows`: Discover workflows usable with `agent_run` operations.
> 
> Parameters:
> 
>   op (string, required): list_agents | list_sessions | get_log | create_session | resume_session | stop_session | cleanup_sessions | list_workflows
>     Operation.
> 
>   limit (integer)
>     [list_sessions, get_log] Max results.
> 
>   model_id (string)
>     [create_session, resume_session] Task label (explore, engineer,
>     pair, design) or specific model_id from list_agents.
> 
>   name (string)
>     [list_sessions] Session name filter.
> 
>   offset (integer)
>     [get_log] Turn offset.
> 
>   session_id (string)
>     [get_log, resume_session, stop_session] Session UUID.
> 
>   session_ids (array<string>)
>     [cleanup_sessions] Array of session UUIDs to delete.
> 
>   session_name (string)
>     [create_session] Display name for a new session.
> 
>   state (string)
>     [list_sessions] Session state filter.
> 
