> agent_run
> ----------------------------------------------------------------------
> Spawn and control Agent Mode sessions. `start` always creates a new session/tab; use `steer` to continue an existing session.
> 
> **Role labels** — pass as `model_id` to auto-select the best agent+model:
> - `explore` — Fast exploration and codebase mapping
> - `engineer` — Balanced engineering work
> - `pair` — Interactive pair programming with highest-tier models
> - `design` — Architecture, design discussions, and creative problem solving
> 
> **Operations**: start | poll | wait | cancel | steer | respond
> 
> - `start`: Launch an agent run in a **new** session/tab. Do NOT pass `session_id` — use `steer` to continue an existing session. Pass `model_id` with a role label or a specific ID from `agent_manage.list_agents`. Returns a `session_id` — save it for all follow-up calls. Waits up to `timeout` seconds (default 300). Pass `detach: true` to return immediately.
> - `poll`: Return current snapshot immediately. Requires `session_id` from a prior start. Returns `interaction_id` when input is pending.
> - `wait`: Block until the run finishes or needs input. Default 300s. `timeout: 0` = poll. Requires `session_id`. Returns `interaction_id` when input is pending.
> - `cancel`: Stop an active agent run. Only valid when the run is `running` or `waiting_for_input`. Requires `session_id`.
> - `steer`: Continue an existing agent session by sending a follow-up instruction to the `session_id` returned by `start`. If the run is still active, the instruction is steered into that run; if the last run already finished, RepoPrompt starts the next run in the same session. Pass `wait: true` (or `timeout_seconds`) to block until the steered run finishes or needs input. Do NOT use `steer` when status is `waiting_for_input` — use `respond` instead.
> - `respond`: Resolve a pending interaction (question, approval, etc). Requires `session_id` and `interaction_id` from the snapshot. The `interaction_id` is returned as a top-level field in poll/wait responses when input is pending.
> 
> **session_id lifecycle**: `start` creates a new session and returns `session_id` in the response. All subsequent operations on that run require passing the same `session_id` back. Do NOT invent session IDs — always use the value returned by `start`.
> 
> **Parallel agents**: When launching multiple agents in parallel, always use `detach: true` so each `start` returns immediately without blocking. You can then `wait` or `poll` each `session_id` independently.
> 
> Parameters:
> 
>   op (string, required): start | poll | wait | cancel | steer | respond
>     Operation.
> 
>   amendment (string)
>     [respond] Amendment text for accept_with_amendment decisions.
> 
>   answers (object)
>     [respond] Structured answers keyed by question ID.
> 
>   detach (boolean)
>     [start] Return immediately instead of waiting. Default false.
> 
>   interaction_id (string)
>     [respond] Pending interaction UUID from the snapshot. Returned as
>     a top-level field in poll/wait responses when the run is
>     waiting_for_input.
> 
>   message (string)
>     [start, steer] Instruction text.
> 
>   model_id (string)
>     [start] Role label (explore, engineer, pair, design) to auto-pick
>     the best agent+model, or a specific model_id from
>     agent_manage.list_agents.
> 
>   response (string)
>     [respond] Text answer or decision token (accept, decline, cancel,
>     skip, etc).
> 
>   session_id (string)
>     [poll, wait, cancel, steer, respond] Session UUID returned by a
>     prior start/steer response. Do not fabricate it. Not accepted by
>     start — use steer to continue an existing session.
> 
>   session_name (string)
>     [start] Display name for a new session.
> 
>   timeout (number)
>     [start, wait] Max wait seconds. 0 = poll. Default 300.
> 
>   timeout_seconds (number)
>     [steer] Max wait seconds when wait=true. 0 = immediate post-steer
>     snapshot. Default 300.
> 
>   wait (boolean)
>     [steer] Wait for an interesting/terminal state after steering.
>     Implied when timeout_seconds is provided.
> 
>   workflow_id (string)
>     [start, steer, respond] Workflow ID. Mutually exclusive with
>     workflow_name.
> 
>   workflow_name (string)
>     [start, steer, respond] Workflow name. Mutually exclusive with
>     workflow_id.
> 
